      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SIR ALEC WHITBY (2) finished second last start over 2100m at Bunbury, beaten 4 metres, after also filling a minor placing at the previous appearance over 2242m at Narrogin. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Meets a similar line up and he can play a big role. LADY OF LEITH (5) finished third last start over 1177m at Pinjarra, beaten 10 metres. That was an improvement on the unplaced effort at this track the run before. Good enough to win a race of this calibre. MARGIMAC (6) should be at her peak for this. Finished third over 2130m here at the latest appearance two weeks ago. Sure to give the top fancies plenty to think about. PAPPINBARRA LADY (4) is in the mix following a fourth at her most recent appearance over 2100m at Bunbury. One for the exotics players.",
